<subSubSection id="E3B45F1ADFEDEBF0F948F5730A7621C1" pageId="null" pageNumber="470" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph id="F3BFEB665F0D1F7033E1147B6BAB583D" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">Ufer-Segge</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="04475344011AEAF9E4C7A847EFC40728" pageId="null" pageNumber="470" type="description">
<paragraph id="45A783C7984E118A5D77E791FDEEDF30" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">
80-150 cm hoch; lange unterirdische 
<normalizedToken id="A6213D3E4E3118592D1E355988FBAC09" originalValue="Ausläufer" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">Auslaeufer</normalizedToken>
treibend. 
<normalizedToken id="AB9DB72198C806A12C7F6D3FD01B512F" originalValue="Grundständige" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">Grundstaendige</normalizedToken>
Blattscheiden wie bei 
<taxonomicName id="730203F74ABA78C5E4B9CF9E1928BD84" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="470" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acutiformis">
<emphasis id="278C8850AFDD73BD1FF0B0A0B381DFC0" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">C. acutiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr.68), jedoch 
<emphasis id="67BF5A3D9CDE51FF8A3073DA9BE4160C" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">dicht gitternervig.</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="58F3E8DDB60E575A08054C300AD8CB64" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
8-15 mm breit, flach, 
<normalizedToken id="9D96DDF1F681F569CFA0ADF5107FF581" originalValue="blaugrün" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">blaugruen</normalizedToken>
, den 
<normalizedToken id="FD91C585ADFE8EA0608A5F9A21F3EE6F" originalValue="Blütenstand" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">Bluetenstand</normalizedToken>
kaum 
<normalizedToken id="537BAA22C17A92182D359B6D257CB510" originalValue="überragend" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">ueberragend</normalizedToken>
. Stengel und 
<normalizedToken id="3C897E21F7131E9428ECC3191C48F82B" originalValue="Blütenstand" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">Bluetenstand</normalizedToken>
wie bei 
<taxonomicName id="1C54DD047BD2F76F73F5BBFC01696FD4" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="470" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acutiformis">
<emphasis id="40F969F39E9F7A5B0EEE298DD74FF13C" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">C. acutiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, die 
<normalizedToken id="5727D2CDF126713CD5AC614F25FF593F" originalValue="Ähren" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">Aehren</normalizedToken>
(mit reifen 
<normalizedToken id="E90849579CAC0F73012122265DB2E246" originalValue="Fruchtschläuchen" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">Fruchtschlaeuchen</normalizedToken>
) jedoch dicker (11-14 mm) und oft 
<normalizedToken id="56431681BE0B265D1720CEEFAAA6BA42" originalValue="länger" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">laenger</normalizedToken>
(bis 10 cm), 
<emphasis id="8E62C5D9094CA0F97E002AC3C851B5DE" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">stets gestielt</emphasis>
(bis 7 cm lang), 
<emphasis id="DA5C498FCA99A2DEE1675B484B39CE3B" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">zur Fruchtzeit nickend.</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="2D2B61AD978A3AF334CE43E5AA1BAEB7" originalValue="Hochblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">Hochblaetter</normalizedToken>
und 
<normalizedToken id="C68E8363A8FA76A9678022D30832F8AB" originalValue="Tragblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">Tragblaetter</normalizedToken>
wie bei 
<emphasis id="6E6A778DE2E8C697CD22B74E63BD0B19" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">
<taxonomicName id="326BE9D0051811B3D5141E6A551C0CAB" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="470" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acutiformis">C. acutiformis</taxonomicName>
. 
<normalizedToken id="5AE12BF75C73889FEA250248FC1FAE97" originalValue="Fruchtschläuche" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">Fruchtschlaeuche</normalizedToken>
5,5
</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="3EE88368925946AB3B75ADB9125F9F26" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">7 mm lang</emphasis>
, etwa in der Mitte am breitesten (2-2,5 mm), im 
<emphasis id="BB5E70D9E46A1298BE8714845ABCEB0D" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">Querschnitt rundlich</emphasis>
(die Frucht eng 
<normalizedToken id="534784AE24711D31F1CAE6D7CF5E9CD5" originalValue="umschließend" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">umschliessend</normalizedToken>
), mit zahlreichen 
<emphasis id="6B7E7C925D7B7040C62954A800CAC1E3" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">vortretenden Nerven</emphasis>
, gelb, 
<emphasis id="A6F89937E048DC8E9D6F3C0211ED9D08" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">
<normalizedToken id="23E35563C69499D97A771B809E35368D" originalValue="glänzend" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">glaenzend</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
, kahl, 
<normalizedToken id="3D68E9A2B1F477F5578F4880A011AA28" originalValue="allmählich" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">allmaehlich</normalizedToken>
in den kurzen, 2 
<normalizedToken id="80E25243A8427490167996C81F728B56" originalValue="zähnigen" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">zaehnigen</normalizedToken>
Schnabel 
<normalizedToken id="B8C6DF8374C7C541A4EED5A009247901" originalValue="verschmälert" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">verschmaelert</normalizedToken>
. Narben 3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A9EB20CE2AFE9DDBF9944A91123816C" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">
<emphasis id="A8BEE8217A6F273C34E568E7EB3B47D3" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">Zytologische Angaben. 2n = 72:</emphasis>
Material aus Schweden (Heilborn 1922Heilborn 1924).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="43A1AA1D2929DEEBA81978D17691F532" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">
<emphasis id="3A22B72B5E30946B9C96EC58B1F1DE23" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">Standort.</emphasis>
Kollin, selten montan. Humose, meist kalkhaltige, 
<normalizedToken id="02DF8D51B844150500409C316FF76FD1" originalValue="nährstoffreiche" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">naehrstoffreiche</normalizedToken>
Boden. 
<normalizedToken id="6C93CA3D51272355835341E5CB756655" originalValue="Großseggengesellschaften" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">Grossseggengesellschaften</normalizedToken>
in der Uferzone stehender und 
<normalizedToken id="9E33EC62138E3C03CB3C185E4DA28717" originalValue="fließender" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">fliessender</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="330E2E5C4CAF855DF535D30390FD19FF" originalValue="Gewässer" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">Gewaesser</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A4CD0AED7D7BFC0ECB31F97ECEB248A" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">
<emphasis id="247CC847D7D0190FD0EF6D645F7FFA10" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">Verbreitung. Eurasiatische Pflanze</emphasis>
(sehr nahe stehende Arten in Nord- und 
<normalizedToken id="55167262EF0A1991040FC2737BF80CD4" originalValue="Südamerika" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">Suedamerika</normalizedToken>
, die von 
<normalizedToken id="A129A0B54CC17D0285CBFDD29DC90BAE" originalValue="Kükenthal" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">Kuekenthal</normalizedToken>
1909 als 
<normalizedToken id="9F8A0B02B2A0AEBDEA78042A015F405D" originalValue="Varietäten" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">Varietaeten</normalizedToken>
von 
<taxonomicName id="923DF572CB8ACC2E96E6FA2BACE1D2DB" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="470" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="riparia">
<emphasis id="FBFFA55FC9A28504E884DE8944950E3A" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">C. riparia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
dargestellt werden): In 
<taxonomicName id="2819106646A9ECD398978B8DFFC603E6" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Europa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="null" pageNumber="470" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Europa</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="D5E70BECCF44561BF89C6688F433F258" originalValue="nordwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">nordwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis 61° NB, in Asien bis ca. 60° NB, 
<normalizedToken id="3CB8257656DB9ADC9D0CC997D77CA492" originalValue="südwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">suedwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis Nordafrika; Kleinasien, Turkestan, 
<normalizedToken id="C80136720F0BCB39AB178287270D97EC" originalValue="ostwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="470">ostwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis Mongolei. Verbreitungskarte von Meusel (1964). - Im Gebiet verbreitet, ziemlich selten.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
